          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "UISwitch"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class declares a property and a method to control its on/off state. As with "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "UISlider"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", when the user manipulates the switch control (“flips” it), it triggers the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uicontrolevents/uicontroleventvaluechanged"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " event."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can customize the appearance of the switch by changing the color used to tint the switch when it is on or off."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For information about basic view behaviors, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "View Programming Guide for iOS",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/WindowsViews/Conceptual/ViewPG_iPhoneOS/Introduction/Introduction.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40009503"
